{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1770143687,"nonce":"LKQIS7b8dxG5ORkDSCbBfMFP6kc=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87oBMNf","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/157","origin":"github"},"title":"Tooling: Create 'read_feature_status' CLI","message":"## Description\nAgents currently struggle to parse the status of a Feature Track issue because it requires reading raw Markdown checkboxes. We need a machine-readable way to get the status.\n\n## Requirements\n1.  **Create script**: `.agent/scripts/read_feature_status.py`\n2.  **Input**: Issue Number (e.g., `--issue 146`)\n3.  **Output**: JSON object containing:\n    - `phase`: Current active phase (int)\n    - `current_task`: Text of the first unchecked task\n    - `status`: 'in_progress', 'blocked', or 'done'\n    - `percent_complete`: Calculated progress\n\n## Parent Issue\nPart of #139","files":null}]}